<inglise> COMMISSION REGULATION (EEC) No 1725/92 of 30 June 1992 laying down detailed implementing rules for the specific measures for supplying the Azores and Madeira with products from the pigmeat sector </inglise>
<eesti> KOMISJONI M&Auml;&Auml;RUS (EM&Uuml;) nr 1725/92 milles s&auml;testatakse sealihasektori toodete Assooridele ja Madeirale tarnimise erimeetmete &uuml;ksikasjalikud rakenduseeskirjad </eesti>
<inglise> THE COMMISSION OF THE EUROPEAN COMMUNITIES, </inglise>
<eesti> 30. juuni 1992 EUROOPA &Uuml;HENDUSTE KOMISJON, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the Treaty establishing the European Economic Community, </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse Euroopa Majandus&uuml;henduse asutamislepingut, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to Council Regulation (EEC) No 1600/92 (1), of 1992, introducing specific measures for the Azores and Madeira concerning certain agricultural products; and in particular Article 10 hereof, </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse n&otilde;ukogu 15. juuni 1992. aasta m&auml;&auml;rust (EM&Uuml;) nr 1600/92, millega teatavate p&otilde;llumajandustoodetega seoses kehtestatakse Assooridele ja Madeirale erimeetmed, eriti selle artiklit 10 </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas in application of Articles 2, 3 and 4 of Council Regulation (EEC) No 1600/92, it is necessary to determine for the pigmeat sector and for the 1992/93 marketing year, on the one hand, the quantities of meat and processed products of the forecast supply balance for Madeira which benefit from an exemption for the levy on direct imports from third countries or from an aid for deliveries originating from the rest of the Community, and on the other hand, the quantities of pure-bred breeding animals originating in the Community which benefit from an aid with a view to developing the potential for production in the Azores and Madeira; </inglise>
<eesti> ning arvestades, et: n&otilde;ukogu m&auml;&auml;ruse (EM&Uuml;) nr 1600/92 artiklite 2, 3 ja 4 kohaldamisel on vaja sealihasektoris majandusaastaks 1992/93 m&auml;&auml;rata &uuml;helt poolt Madeira hinnangulise tarnebilansi sealiha ja t&ouml;&ouml;deldud sealiha kogused, mis kolmandatest riikidest otse impordituna on tollimaksust vabastatud v&otilde;i mujalt &uuml;hendusest p&auml;rinevatena saavad tarneabi, ning teiselt poolt &uuml;hendusest p&auml;rit puhtat&otilde;uliste t&otilde;uloomade arv, kelle eest antakse Assooride ja Madeira tootmispotentsiaali arendamiseks abi; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas it is appropriate to fix the amount of the aids referred to above for the supply to the archipelagos, on the one hand, in meat and, on the other hand, of breeding animals originating in the rest of the Community; whereas these aids must be fixed taking into account in particular the costs of supply from the world market, conditions due to the geographical situation of the archipelagos and the basis of the current prices on export to third countries for the animals or products concerned; </inglise>
<eesti> on asjakohane kinnitada eespool nimetatud abi summad &uuml;helt poolt liha ning teiselt poolt &uuml;hendusest p&auml;rit t&otilde;uloomade saartele tarnimisel; nende abisummade kinnitamisel tuleb eelk&otilde;ige arvesse v&otilde;tta maailmaturult tarnimise kulu, saarte geograafilisest asendist tulenevaid tingimusi ning asjaomaste loomade ja toodete kolmandasse riikidesse eksportimisel kehtivaid hindu; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas the common detailed implementing rules for the supply regime for the Azores and Madeira for certain agricultural products were laid down by Commission Regulation (EEC) No 1696/92 (2); whereas it is appropriate to lay down complementary implementing rules adjusted in the light of current commercial practices in the pigmeat sector in particular regarding the duration of the validity of import certificates and the aid, the amount of the securities ensuring compliance with their obligations by operators; </inglise>
<eesti> teatavate p&otilde;llumajandussaaduste Assooridele ja Madeirale tarnimise korra &uuml;hised &uuml;ksikasjalikud rakenduseeskirjad on kehtestatud komisjoni m&auml;&auml;rusega (EM&Uuml;) nr 1696/92; on asjakohane kehtestada t&auml;iendavad rakenduseeskirjad, mida on kohandatud koosk&otilde;las sealihasektoris kehtivatele kaubandustavadega, eelk&otilde;ige seoses impordisertifikaatide ja abi kehtivusaja ning ettev&otilde;tjate kohustuste t&auml;itmist garanteerivate tagatiste summadega; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas with view to efficiently managing the supply regime, it is necessary to provide for a time limit for the making of requests for certificates and a period of reflection for the delivery of the latter; </inglise>
<eesti> tarnekorra t&otilde;husa toimimise huvides on vaja s&auml;testada sertifikaaditaotluste esitamist&auml;htaeg ning otsustamisaeg sertifikaatide v&auml;ljastamiseks; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas in application of Council Regulation (EEC) No 1600/92, the supply regime is applicable from 1 July 1992; whereas it is necessary to provide for application of the detailed implementing rules from the same date; </inglise>
<eesti> komisjoni m&auml;&auml;ruse (EM&Uuml;) nr 1600/92 kohaldamisel kehtib tarnekord alates 1. juulist 1992; on vaja s&auml;testada &uuml;ksikasjalike rakenduseeskirjade kohaldamine samast kuup&auml;evast; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas the measures provided for in the present regulation are in conformity with the opinion of the Management Committee for Pigmeat, </inglise>
<eesti> k&auml;esolevas m&auml;&auml;ruses s&auml;testatud meetmed on koosk&otilde;las sealihaturu korralduskomitee arvamusega, </eesti>
<inglise> HAS ADOPTED THIS REGULATION: </inglise>
<eesti> ON VASTU V&Otilde;TNUD K&Auml;ESOLEVA M&Auml;&Auml;RUSE. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 1 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 1 </eesti>
<inglise> Pursuant to Article 2 of Regulation (EEC) No 1600/92, the quantities of the forecast supply balance for Madeira with products from the pigmeat sector which benefit from the exoneration from the import levy on products coming from third countries or which benefit from Community aid are fixed in Annex I. </inglise>
<eesti> M&auml;&auml;ruse (EM&Uuml;) nr 1600/92 artikli 2 kohaselt on I lisas esitatud Madeira hinnangulises tarnebilansis kindlaksm&auml;&auml;ratud sealihasektori toodete kogused, mis on vabastatud kolmandatest riikidest p&auml;rit toodetele kehtestatud impordimaksust v&otilde;i saavad &uuml;henduse abi. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 2 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 2 </eesti>
<inglise> 1. </inglise>
<eesti> 1. </eesti>
<inglise> The aid provided for in Article 3 (2) of Regulation (EEC) No 1600/92 for products included in the forecast supply balance and which come from the Community market is fixed in Annex II. </inglise>
<eesti> M&auml;&auml;ruse (EM&Uuml;) nr 1600/92 artikli 3 l&otilde;ikes 2 s&auml;testatud abi hinnangulises tarnebilansis sisalduvate ning &uuml;henduse turult p&auml;rit toodete eest on kinnitatud II lisas. </eesti>
<inglise> 2. </inglise>
<eesti> 2. </eesti>
<inglise> Products benefitting from the aid are specified in accordance with the provisions of Commission Regulation (EEC) No 3846/87 (1) and in particular Annex VII. </inglise>
<eesti> Tooted, mille eest abi antakse, on t&auml;psustatud koosk&otilde;las komisjoni m&auml;&auml;ruse (EM&Uuml;) nr 3846/87, eelk&otilde;ige nimetatud m&auml;&auml;ruse VII lisa s&auml;tetega. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 3 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 3 </eesti>
<inglise> The aid provided for in Article 4 (1) of Regulation (EEC) No 1600/92 for the supply to the Azores and Madeira of pure-bred breeding pigs originating from the Community as well as the number of animals which benefit from it are fixed in Annex III. </inglise>
<eesti> M&auml;&auml;ruse (EM&Uuml;) nr 1600/92 artikli 4 l&otilde;ikes 1 s&auml;testatud abi &uuml;hendusest p&auml;rit puhtat&otilde;uliste t&otilde;usigade Assooridele ja Madeirale tarnimiseks, samuti loomade arv, kelle eest abi antakse, on kinnitatud III lisas. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 4 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 4 </eesti>
<inglise> Portugal shall designate the competent authority for: </inglise>
<eesti> Portugal m&auml;&auml;rab p&auml;deva asutuse, mis: </eesti>
<inglise> (a) the delivery of import certificates; </inglise>
<eesti> a) v&auml;ljastab impordisertifikaate; </eesti>
<inglise> (b) the delivery of the aid certificate provided for in Article 4 (1) of Regulation (EEC) No 1696/92; </inglise>
<eesti> b) v&auml;ljastab m&auml;&auml;ruse (EM&Uuml;) nr 1696/92 artikli 4 l&otilde;ikes 1 s&auml;testatud abisertifikaadi; </eesti>
<inglise> (c) the payment of the aid to the operators concerned. </inglise>
<eesti> c) maksab asjaomastele ettev&otilde;tjatele abi v&auml;lja. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 5 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 5 </eesti>
<inglise> The provisions of Regulation (EEC) No 1696/92 shall apply. </inglise>
<eesti> Kohaldatakse m&auml;&auml;ruse (EM&Uuml;) nr 1696/92 s&auml;tteid. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 6 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 6 </eesti>
<inglise> 1. </inglise>
<eesti> 1. </eesti>
<inglise> Requests for certificates shall be presented to the competent authority during the first five working days of every month. </inglise>
<eesti> Sertifikaaditaotlused esitatakse p&auml;devale asutusele iga kuu esimese viie t&ouml;&ouml;p&auml;eva jooksul. </eesti>
<inglise> A request for a certificate shall only be valid if: </inglise>
<eesti> Taotlus kehtib ainult siis, kui: </eesti>
<inglise> (a) it does not exceed the maximum quantity available for each group of products published by Portugal; </inglise>
<eesti> a) selles ei &uuml;letata Portugali poolt iga tootegrupi kohta avaldatud maksimumkogust; </eesti>
<inglise> (b) before the expiry of the period provided for the presentation of requests for certificates, the proof has been provided that the interested party has lodged a security of ECU 30 per 100 kg. </inglise>
<eesti> b) enne taotluste esitamist&auml;htaja l&otilde;ppu on t&otilde;endatud, et huvitatud pool on andnud tagatise summas 30 ek&uuml;&uuml;d 100 kilogrammi kohta. </eesti>
<inglise> 2. </inglise>
<eesti> 2. </eesti>
<inglise> Certificates shall be delivered on the 10th working day of every month. </inglise>
<eesti> Sertifikaadid v&auml;ljastatakse iga kuu 10. t&ouml;&ouml;p&auml;eval. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 7 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 7 </eesti>
<inglise> 1. </inglise>
<eesti> 1. </eesti>
<inglise> The duration of validity of import certificates shall expire on the last day of the month following that of their delivery. </inglise>
<eesti> Impordisertifikaatide kehtivusaeg l&otilde;peb nende v&auml;ljastamise kuule j&auml;rgneva kuu viimasel p&auml;eval. </eesti>
<inglise> 2. </inglise>
<eesti> 2. </eesti>
<inglise> The duration of validity of the aid certificates shall expire on the last day of the second month following that of their delivery. </inglise>
<eesti> Abisertifikaatide kehtivusaeg l&otilde;peb nende v&auml;ljastamise kuule j&auml;rgneva teise kuu viimasel p&auml;eval. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 8 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 8 </eesti>
<inglise> The payment of aid provided for in Article 2 and 3 shall be made for quantities actually supplied. </inglise>
<eesti> Artiklites 2 ja 3 s&auml;testatud abi makstakse tegelikult tarnitud koguste pealt. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 9 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 9 </eesti>
<inglise> The amount of aid referred to in Articles 2 and 3 shall be altered when the market situation makes this necessary. </inglise>
<eesti> Artiklites 2 ja 3 s&auml;testatud abi summat muudetakse, kui turuolukord seda n&otilde;uab. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 10 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 10 </eesti>
<inglise> This Regulation shall enter into force on the day of its publication in the Official Journal of the European Communities. This Regulation shall be binding in its entirety and directly applicable in all Member States. </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esolev m&auml;&auml;rus j&otilde;ustub j&auml;rgmisel p&auml;eval p&auml;rast selle avaldamist Euroopa &Uuml;henduste Teatajas. </eesti>
